  <note>
   <p>The following documentation focuses on the classic UI. For information about authoring in the modern, touch-based UI, see the <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/author.md">standard Authoring documentation</a>.</p> 
  </note>
  <p>The author environment allows you to perform tasks related to:</p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/author.md">Authoring</a> (including <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/page-authoring.md">page authoring</a> and <a href="/assets/using/author-assets">managing assets</a>)<br /> </li> 
   <li><a href="/sites/administering/using/administer">Administering</a> tasks you need when generating and maintaining the content on your website </li> 
  </ul> 
  <p>Two graphical user interfaces are provided to achieve this, these are accessible through any modern browser:</p> 
  <ol>
   <li><p>Classic UI</p> 
    <ul> 
     <li>This UI has always been available in AEM for many years.</li> 
     <li>It is predominantly green.</li> 
     <li>It was designed for use on desktop devices.</li> 
     <li>It is no longer maintained.</li> 
     <li>The following documentation focuses on this classic UI. For information about authoring in the modern, touch-based UI, see the <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/author.md">standard Authoring documentation</a>.</li> 
    </ul> <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/chlimage_1-164.png" /></li>
   <li><p>Touch-Optimized UI</p> 
    <ul> 
     <li>This is the modern, standard AEM UI.</li> 
     <li>It is predominantly grey, with a clean, flat interface.</li> 
     <li>It is designed for use on both touch and desktop devices (optimized for touch). The look and feel is the same on all devices, though <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/basic-handling.md#viewingandselectingyourresources">viewing and selecting your resources</a> differs slightly (taps versus clicks).</li> 
     <li>See the <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/author.md">standard Authoring documentation</a> for further details on how to author using the touch-based UI. The following documentaiton focuses on the classic UI.
